1
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:14,416
Abe no Seimei?

2
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,166
[GRANDPA MIYAKO] Yes. Known as
a powerful onmyoji

3
00:00:17,250 --> 00:00:18,500
from the Heian Period.

4
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:21,000
And our family, the Miyako clan,

5
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:22,875
all bear his bloodline.

6
00:00:22,958 --> 00:00:23,916
[YOUNG ARATA grumbles]

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,708
I have many stories

8
00:00:25,791 --> 00:00:27,208
about how amazing he was.

9
00:00:27,291 --> 00:00:28,625
Let's see, there was once--

10
00:00:28,708 --> 00:00:29,625
[YOUNG ARATA] It's okay.

11
00:00:29,708 --> 00:00:31,750
I'm gonna go play over there.

12
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:33,166
[GRANDPA MIYAKO]
Wait. Arata!

13
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:35,000
Arata!

14
00:00:35,083 --> 00:00:37,416
[OLD TENGU]
No, Seimei!

15
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:39,500
-[YOUNG ARATA] Huh?
-Seimei!

16
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:42,291
I know a Seimei when I see one!

17
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,083
It's your blood!

18
00:00:44,166 --> 00:00:45,916
It smells the same as his!

19
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,291
This must be a mistake. I--

20
00:00:48,375 --> 00:00:49,666
-[barks]
-Aah!

21
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:51,291
[screams, gasps]

22
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:52,875
[THEO]
Mornin', sunshine.

23
00:00:52,958 --> 00:00:54,666
Well, look who's awake.

24
00:00:56,041 --> 00:00:57,916
Okay... I guess?

25
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:02,708
[KYOICHI] You collapsed at
the Citizen's Plaza last night.

26
00:01:02,791 --> 00:01:04,916
It's understandable, I guess.

27
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:08,250
Sounds to me like
you had a busy night.

28
00:01:09,458 --> 00:01:12,250
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm head
of the Nocturnal Community

29
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,541
Relations Division.

30
00:01:13,625 --> 00:01:14,958
My name's Senda.

31
00:01:15,041 --> 00:01:17,000
Introducing our boss.

32
00:01:17,083 --> 00:01:19,250
[ARATA]
Oh, it's nice to meet you, sir.

33
00:01:19,333 --> 00:01:22,916
I was planning on making our
introductions tomorrow, but...

34
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,333
Arata Miyako, is it?

35
00:01:24,416 --> 00:01:27,708
So, you've got Ears of Sand,
I've heard.

36
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:02,250
♪

37
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:03,625
[THEO]
So, basically,

38
00:03:03,708 --> 00:03:05,500
it's when you can
miraculously understand

39
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:07,583
a random language
you've never heard before.

40
00:03:07,666 --> 00:03:10,541
We call it
The Ears of Sand!

41
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:12,500
Does that sound like something
that's ever happened to you

42
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:14,125
when talking to
a foreign stranger?

43
00:03:14,208 --> 00:03:17,041
-I don't think so.
-[THEO] Interesting.

44
00:03:17,125 --> 00:03:19,291
So it doesn't happen
with human languages, then.

45
00:03:19,375 --> 00:03:22,500
Yet you understand
the Anothers perfectly. Huh.

46
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:24,791
Looks like you've discovered
an exceptional new member.

47
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,291
Yeah, I know.

48
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:29,041
[ARATA] So, um, if you can't
understand the Anothers,

49
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:31,083
how have you been able to deal
with them for this long?

50
00:03:31,166 --> 00:03:34,333
Facial expressions,
mannerisms, patterns.

51
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:37,041
Same way you might try
with a cat or a dog.

52
00:03:37,125 --> 00:03:39,708
-Huh?
-This is a first.

53
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:41,541
I've never known anyone
in our line of work

54
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:42,625
who could hear them.

55
00:03:42,708 --> 00:03:44,208
Unless, well,

56
00:03:44,291 --> 00:03:46,125
I was going to say
maybe before our time,

57
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:48,500
but I don't think
there are any past records.

58
00:03:51,458 --> 00:03:52,833
[SENDA] I wonder if it has
anything to do

59
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:55,041
with the way they call you
Abe no Seimei?

60
00:03:56,083 --> 00:03:57,916
Got any idea
what that could mean?

61
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:02,291
My grandpa said
something about it.

62
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:04,833
And our family,
the Miyako clan,

63
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:06,625
all bear his bloodline.

64
00:04:07,916 --> 00:04:09,750
None of us
ever took him seriously.

65
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:11,500
[SENDA]
Hmm.

66
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:14,083
Well, since your shift is over,

67
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:16,458
why don't you go home
and get a little rest?

68
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:17,750
Have a good night.

69
00:04:20,541 --> 00:04:21,583
[ARATA sighs]

70
00:04:21,666 --> 00:04:23,916
[THEO]
That was weird, wasn't it?

71
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,500
[KYOICHI] Yeah, what's the deal
with that kid?

72
00:04:27,625 --> 00:04:29,166
[SENDA]
Abe no Seimei, huh?

73
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:32,208
Isn't the exam supposed
to weed out anyone

74
00:04:32,291 --> 00:04:35,375
who had prior relationships
or experiences like that?

75
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:39,208
Huh?

76
00:04:39,291 --> 00:04:40,875
You're here to investigate?

77
00:04:40,958 --> 00:04:43,291
Well, and to bring a gift.

78
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:46,833
If we can find out your
connection to Abe no Seimei,

79
00:04:46,916 --> 00:04:48,500
that could help us determine
whether or not

80
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:51,541
the Ears of Sand are real,
according to Senda, anyway.

81
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:52,791
[ARATA] Huh?

82
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,833
Okay. Sure.

83
00:04:54,916 --> 00:04:57,541
[GIRL] What's this?
Arata has visitors?

84
00:04:58,875 --> 00:05:00,458
[ARATA]
Oh, hi, Izumi.

85
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,250
New co-workers?

86
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:05,041
It's a pleasure
to meet Arata's friends.

87
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,833
My name's Izumi.

88
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:09,125
[ARATA] Her parents own
a great restaurant nearby.

89
00:05:09,208 --> 00:05:11,916
And this is Sakaki.
We work together.

90
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,625
Excuse me, my name's Theo.

91
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,625
His superior. Pleasure.

92
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:19,625
Hmm?
Superior? Really?

93
00:05:19,708 --> 00:05:20,958
That's right.

94
00:05:21,041 --> 00:05:23,333
Theo's been with us
as long as Chief Senda.

95
00:05:23,416 --> 00:05:24,958
[ARATA]
What? I had no idea!

96
00:05:25,041 --> 00:05:26,583
[THEO] So, you have to do
whatever I say.

97
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:27,833
[KYOICHI]
Most people are surprised

98
00:05:27,916 --> 00:05:29,166
the first time
he tells them that.

99
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:30,541
[IZUMI]
Hey, you're doing something

100
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:33,333
for the government
on the night shift, right?

101
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:34,875
[ARATA]
Yeah, why?

102
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:35,791
[IZUMI gasps]

103
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:40,000
Is it something kinky?

104
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:41,208
[ARATA]
Uh...

105
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:45,208
[ARATA] I think all my grandpa's
belongings are still in here.

106
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:47,791
I haven't opened it
in a really long time.

107
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:50,083
This brings back
so many memories.

108
00:05:50,166 --> 00:05:52,541
I used to play in here
when my grandparents were alive.

109
00:05:52,625 --> 00:05:56,041
When my family and I moved in
after they passed away,

110
00:05:56,125 --> 00:05:57,333
I just kinda stopped.

111
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:02,833
[THEO]
Whoa, holy crap!

112
00:06:04,041 --> 00:06:06,041
My parents said you can take
whatever you want.

113
00:06:06,125 --> 00:06:07,833
That's amazing!

114
00:06:07,916 --> 00:06:09,583
Okay, I'm gonna go
check upstairs.

115
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:12,416
[KYOICHI] I guess we should
at least take all the papers,

116
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,333
Sure. Uh...

117
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:17,333
♪

118
00:06:17,416 --> 00:06:19,541
It's a cat?

119
00:06:19,625 --> 00:06:23,583
♪

120
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:25,000
[gasps]

121
00:06:26,541 --> 00:06:27,958
Huh? It stood!

122
00:06:28,041 --> 00:06:31,041
Arata!

123
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:32,291
[ARATA grunts]

124
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:34,500
You're back!
I missed you!

125
00:06:34,583 --> 00:06:36,375
-You smell so good!
-[THEO] What's going on?

126
00:06:36,458 --> 00:06:39,875
Uh, it's an Another,
who's obsessed with Arata.

127
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:41,041
[THEO] Huh?

128
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:42,666
[KYOICHI]
It has two tails.

129
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:44,541
A nekomata.

130
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:46,541
How could you
possibly know my name?

131
00:06:47,541 --> 00:06:48,708
[YUKI]
Don't you remember?

132
00:06:48,791 --> 00:06:50,500
We used to play together
all the time!

133
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:55,375
[ARATA]
A white cat.

134
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:57,875
With blue eyes.

135
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:01,166
-Yuki?
-Yes!

136
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:03,583
[YUKI] I'm so happy
to see you again, Arata!

137
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:05,583
[THEO]
Hello!

138
00:07:05,666 --> 00:07:07,958
I could use some help up here!

139
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:10,458
Why is that nekomata
insanely huge?

140
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:12,416
Arata. You okay?

141
00:07:13,416 --> 00:07:14,375
[ARATA]
Yeah.

142
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:18,875
[YUKI] What are you
doing here, Arata?

143
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:21,666
We came to get a few
of the old books

144
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:22,875
for a little research.

145
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:24,166
[YUKI]
You can't do that!

146
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,791
Your ancestors told me
to protect

147
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:27,208
everything in this storehouse.

148
00:07:27,291 --> 00:07:30,333
And that's what I plan to do,
no matter what.

149
00:07:30,416 --> 00:07:31,875
[ARATA]
Ancestors?

150
00:07:31,958 --> 00:07:34,458
[YUKI] Your grandpa's
grandpa's grandpa.

151
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:36,250
It goes a very long way back.

152
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:38,750
Ages. He was my former owner.

153
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:42,083
You mean,
you've been here that long?

154
00:07:42,166 --> 00:07:43,291
[YUKI]
I have.

155
00:07:43,375 --> 00:07:45,500
But over the last century or so,

156
00:07:45,583 --> 00:07:47,875
you've been the only one
that's been able to see me.

157
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:50,291
[ARATA]
Poor guy.

158
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:53,791
So, all this time,

159
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:56,375
Yuki's been in here alone.

160
00:07:56,458 --> 00:07:58,500
Just protecting the storehouse.

161
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:03,666
♪

162
00:08:04,875 --> 00:08:06,916
[ARATA sighs]
Why don't you come with us

163
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,375
and watch over the books
from there?

164
00:08:08,458 --> 00:08:12,250
You've gotta be bored
of this place by now.

165
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:14,666
The grandparents that I remember
would've never wanted you

166
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:17,791
to spend an eternity
in a dark house like this.

167
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:19,000
[YUKI]
But...

168
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,250
[ARATA]
Please come.

169
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,458
I want you there.

170
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:24,333
That okay?

171
00:08:27,875 --> 00:08:31,125
[YUKI]
Arata! I'm so happy!

172
00:08:31,208 --> 00:08:33,291
I was... I was so...

173
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:35,666
so lonely...

174
00:08:36,666 --> 00:08:38,333
in here all by myself.

175
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:40,458
I'm sorry, Yuki.

176
00:08:41,583 --> 00:08:43,708
I wish I'd gotten
to you sooner somehow.

177
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:49,416
Being alone is hard.

178
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:55,125
♪

179
00:09:01,125 --> 00:09:02,375
[YUKI]
This place is huge!

180
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:04,458
And there's so much light!

181
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:06,458
It's nothing like
the storehouse!

182
00:09:06,541 --> 00:09:08,541
I was hoping you'd like it.

183
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:11,041
-[TAROBO] Hey, over here!
-[ARATA] Huh?

184
00:09:11,125 --> 00:09:12,208
[TAROBO]
Other way. Up.

185
00:09:12,291 --> 00:09:13,958
[ARATA]
Huh?

186
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:16,208
[TAROBO]
Arata Miyako, right?

187
00:09:16,291 --> 00:09:18,750
[YUKI]
Hold on, you know him?

188
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:21,041
[ARATA]
Sure. Taro-- Uh?

189
00:09:21,125 --> 00:09:23,500
Those bruises!
What happened?

190
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:26,791
Well, I got into a fight.
A big one.

191
00:09:27,958 --> 00:09:30,625
Everybody's against my love
for an angel.

192
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:33,166
Father is always fighting
with her sisters.

193
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:36,583
To be honest, I'm not sure
what's going to happen now.

194
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:40,958
But you're different.
You believed in our love.

195
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:42,958
You rooted for us.

196
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:45,875
[laughs softly]
And why not?

197
00:09:45,958 --> 00:09:47,750
I thought you two
made a nice couple.

198
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:50,208
That's nice to hear.

199
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:51,750
Means more than
you'll ever know.

200
00:09:53,166 --> 00:09:56,541
So, uh... thanks
for your kindness.

201
00:09:58,375 --> 00:09:59,250
Huh?

202
00:10:06,041 --> 00:10:07,958
[YUKI]
You've made me happy, too!

203
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:10,083
I can finally talk to you.

204
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:13,041
I've always wished I could.

205
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:16,083
Yeah. Me, too.

206
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:21,458
♪

207
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:23,250
[inaudible]

208
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:36,791
[MAN] The Anothers are
pretty quiet tonight,

209
00:10:36,875 --> 00:10:38,166
aren't they?

210
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,833
I wish it were
always like this.

211
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:43,166
Huh? What is that?

212
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:45,583
A bird?

213
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,916
Can't be, it's way too big.

214
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,458
Is there something
on top of it?

215
00:10:50,541 --> 00:10:52,500
A person?

216
00:10:58,208 --> 00:10:59,458
Good morning, how are you?

217
00:10:59,541 --> 00:11:01,375
Hey there. Welcome back.

218
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:03,333
Looks like we have
everybody here now.

219
00:11:03,416 --> 00:11:05,041
Which is great
because there's something

220
00:11:05,125 --> 00:11:06,833
we need to deal
with immediately.

221
00:11:08,541 --> 00:11:11,541
On the Shibuya Ward side of
the Shinjuku Imperial Gardens,

222
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:13,458
someone reported
spotting a kisha.

223
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:15,000
Hmm? A kisha?

224
00:11:16,083 --> 00:11:17,458
[THEO]
This is what it looks like.

225
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:18,875
They're Chinese Anothers.

226
00:11:18,958 --> 00:11:21,000
Monstrous birds
that bring disaster.

227
00:11:21,083 --> 00:11:23,291
It's got ten necks
but only nine heads.

228
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:25,000
Some call it
a nine-headed bird.

229
00:11:25,083 --> 00:11:27,666
Thing is, we've actually
been getting reports

230
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:29,708
of sightings for a while now.

231
00:11:29,791 --> 00:11:32,208
In January,
it was seen in Kyoto.

232
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:33,791
February, it was Aichi,

233
00:11:33,875 --> 00:11:35,458
and it just keeps
heading east from there.

234
00:11:35,541 --> 00:11:37,666
It was in Aichi in February?

235
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,250
[SENDA]
Yep. The Izuna incident.

236
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:42,041
What are you guys
talking about? Izuna?

237
00:11:42,125 --> 00:11:44,166
[THEO]
Hang on. Watch this first.

238
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:46,458
[MAN]
Do we really have to do this?

239
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:48,916
[THEO] An Izuna is a type
of weasel Another.

240
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,166
Its tail is made
of a metal so flexible

241
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:52,750
it's called, "living iron."

242
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:55,458
-[IZUNA squeaking]
-Many like to use it in rituals.

243
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:58,250
-[MAN] Is that them?
-[liquid splatters]

244
00:11:58,333 --> 00:11:59,541
Huh?

245
00:12:00,708 --> 00:12:02,666
[gasps]
It-it's blood!

246
00:12:05,541 --> 00:12:07,250
[SENDA]
Is it making sense, Arata?

247
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:09,750
There was a time
when several Izuna were found

248
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,708
with their tails cut off
in the Aichi Prefecture.

249
00:12:12,791 --> 00:12:15,000
That was the Izuna Incident.

250
00:12:15,083 --> 00:12:16,541
But there's more
to it than that.

251
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:20,291
[ARATA]
Hmm? The same one as before?

252
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:22,875
Yeah, and it was seen
very recently.

253
00:12:23,875 --> 00:12:25,541
Your assignment is
to head out to the gardens

254
00:12:25,625 --> 00:12:27,166
and look for traces
of the kisha.

255
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:28,916
Shouldn't be
too difficult to track,

256
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,458
with one of its necks
bleeding constantly.

257
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:39,208
[ARATA]
Look at all that blood.

258
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:41,041
Mission accomplished.

259
00:12:41,125 --> 00:12:43,625
Is this kisha that bad?
Honestly.

260
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:45,208
[KYOICHI] This blood
on the ground

261
00:12:45,291 --> 00:12:46,791
will excite the Anothers.

262
00:12:46,875 --> 00:12:48,958
If a kisha shows up,
it's only a matter of time

263
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:50,916
before our
Another troubles multiply.

264
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,583
[ARATA]
Yeah, that is bad.

265
00:12:52,666 --> 00:12:55,916
All we can do is be careful
and collect overtime.

266
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:59,875
Overtime, and hope that it goes
away as soon as possible.

267
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:02,041
Couldn't we talk
to it directly?

268
00:13:02,125 --> 00:13:03,041
[BOTH]
Huh?

269
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:05,916
Well, since I can understand it,

270
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,291
I could ask it to leave?

271
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:09,541
Maybe it doesn't know
it's causing a problem?

272
00:13:09,625 --> 00:13:11,041
[THEO laughing]

273
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:13,333
Arata, you can't reason with it.

274
00:13:13,416 --> 00:13:14,875
It's not a person.

275
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:17,000
[THEO] That's like trying
to explain to a typhoon

276
00:13:17,083 --> 00:13:19,166
that residential areas
are inappropriate places

277
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:20,875
-to throw tantrums.
-But I--

278
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:23,666
It's a side effect
of the Ears of Sand.

279
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:25,500
You have the ability
to understand them,

280
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:27,333
and that boosts your confidence.

281
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:30,208
It tricks you into thinking
you can trust them.

282
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:32,583
What are you going to do when
you ask them politely to stop

283
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:35,000
and they agree,
in exchange for your life?

284
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:39,500
[KYOICHI] Human common sense
doesn't translate for them.

285
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:41,625
You know what would help?

286
00:13:41,708 --> 00:13:43,041
If you researched
the scarier traits

287
00:13:43,125 --> 00:13:44,041
of the Anothers.

288
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:48,541
Anothers aren't capable
of human common sense. Right.

289
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:50,833
[FAIRY 1] I guess this means
we can't fly for a while.

290
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:52,500
[FAIRY 2]
How can someone be so terrible?

291
00:13:52,583 --> 00:13:53,833
[FAIRY 1]
You're right. We'll stay low.

292
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:55,375
[FAIRY 3] There's no way
we can fight them.

293
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:58,583
We could be attacked by a cat
or something down here.

294
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:01,583
Why can't you fly?

295
00:14:01,666 --> 00:14:03,000
[PIXIES]
He found us!

296
00:14:03,083 --> 00:14:04,916
-It's a human. What do we do?
-Let's run!

297
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,708
We'll have to run
if we can't fly!

298
00:14:06,791 --> 00:14:08,541
[gasps]
I know him!

299
00:14:08,625 --> 00:14:11,041
He's the lowest one in the ranks
at Shinjuku City Hall!

300
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:12,375
-He's the lowest?
-The lowest!

301
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:14,208
Hey! Listen, you guys!

302
00:14:14,291 --> 00:14:15,666
[KYOICHI]
What's going on over there?

303
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,000
The fairies!

304
00:14:17,083 --> 00:14:18,250
They're all upset about

305
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:20,416
not being able to fly
for some reason?

306
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,083
We need powder for our wings.

307
00:14:22,166 --> 00:14:24,625
But some strange person
stole all the powder we had.

308
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:26,625
They were riding on
the back of a giant bird.

309
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:29,208
I say it was a fancy man
with long hair!

310
00:14:29,291 --> 00:14:30,958
[FAIRY 2] No, it was a woman
with dark hair!

311
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:33,791
[FAIRY 1] They had the golden
shimmering eyes of a beast!

312
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:37,333
[ARATA] At least, that's how
the fairies explained it.

313
00:14:37,416 --> 00:14:39,875
So, there was
an Another on a kisha?

314
00:14:39,958 --> 00:14:41,708
That may be where
the problem lies.

315
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:44,208
Excuse me, guys.

316
00:14:44,291 --> 00:14:46,291
Sorry to ask this of you
when you just got back,

317
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:48,458
but can you go
to the Kanoichi Bunko?

318
00:14:48,541 --> 00:14:49,583
Why Kanoichi?

319
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:50,833
All they would tell me

320
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:52,041
is that they need
Arata's ears

321
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:53,458
as quickly as possible.

322
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:54,625
But whatever it is,

323
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:56,250
it results in them
owing us one.

324
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:57,875
I'll get you the paperwork.

325
00:14:59,083 --> 00:15:00,916
[KYOICHI] Kanoichi Bunko
Publishing is said to have

326
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,416
basically anything
you'd like to learn

327
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,000
about various eastern magics.

328
00:15:04,083 --> 00:15:06,958
They're an old clan of onmyoji,

329
00:15:07,041 --> 00:15:08,833
and the entire family
is quite skilled

330
00:15:08,916 --> 00:15:10,500
in the crafting
of magical tools.

331
00:15:10,583 --> 00:15:13,291
So they've fused British magic
with Japanese items.

332
00:15:13,375 --> 00:15:15,666
[THEO] Everything they make
is for dealing with Anothers.

333
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:17,666
Here, read this.

334
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,541
Oh. Thank you.

335
00:15:19,625 --> 00:15:21,166
It sounds like
they were robbed.

336
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:22,625
Luckily, an Another close by

337
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:24,291
saw the whole thing
when it happened.

338
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:26,958
So, I'll bet they want
to use your Ears of Sand

339
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:28,666
to interpret its report.

340
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:29,791
[ARATA]
Huh.

341
00:15:31,791 --> 00:15:32,791
Welcome.

342
00:15:32,875 --> 00:15:34,833
My name's Akane Kanoichi.

343
00:15:34,916 --> 00:15:36,416
I'm with the Chiyoda division.

344
00:15:37,416 --> 00:15:40,541
I really appreciate you coming
so far out of your way

345
00:15:40,625 --> 00:15:42,458
to help our branch
with this matter.

346
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:45,000
Please. You're always doing
so much for us.

347
00:15:46,416 --> 00:15:48,458
[AKANE]
And you must be Arata Miyako,

348
00:15:48,541 --> 00:15:49,833
-is that right?
-Oh, yes!

349
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:52,250
Everyone's been talking
about your gift.

350
00:15:52,333 --> 00:15:54,291
Even all the way out here
in the Chiyoda ward.

351
00:15:55,333 --> 00:15:57,125
Thank you
for coming here today.

352
00:15:58,125 --> 00:15:59,125
You're welcome.

353
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:04,625
[door opens]

354
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:16,416
[ARATA]
Who's that?

355
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,791
Protector and goddess
of the Kanoichi.

356
00:16:20,125 --> 00:16:22,291
[KYOICHI]
Is that a zashiki warashi?

357
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:23,833
[AKANE]
Yes, you're exactly right.

358
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:26,625
[THEO] How'd you get her
to agree to be your house god?

359
00:16:26,708 --> 00:16:29,625
Zashiki warashi are supposed
to be impossible to bind.

360
00:16:29,708 --> 00:16:33,208
Yes, I know. We are
very fortunate to have her.

361
00:16:33,291 --> 00:16:36,041
She agreed to stay in accordance
with an ancient contract.

362
00:16:36,125 --> 00:16:37,708
[THEO]
What contract?

363
00:16:37,791 --> 00:16:39,375
[AKANE]
Once every ten years,

364
00:16:39,458 --> 00:16:41,291
it is our duty to cut her hair.

365
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:45,791
We offer up a dagger made
with the Kanoichi's arts

366
00:16:45,875 --> 00:16:46,791
as part of a barrier.

367
00:16:48,666 --> 00:16:51,250
She told us she would like
to seal away something

368
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:53,000
beneath the items.

369
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:55,000
[KYOICHI]
So, you want Arata's help

370
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,750
with something involving
this ritual?

371
00:16:57,833 --> 00:17:00,375
[AKANE] Yes. If we don't get
the stolen hair back,

372
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:01,583
the seal will be weakened.

373
00:17:01,666 --> 00:17:03,291
-[GIRL] The oni.
-Huh?

374
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:04,791
The oni is coming.

375
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:06,791
-The bad oni.
-[ARATA] Huh?

376
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:09,375
-Oni?
-[gasps] You heard that?

377
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:11,541
You can understand me, mister?

378
00:17:11,625 --> 00:17:12,750
Uh, yeah.

379
00:17:14,208 --> 00:17:15,750
I'm Arata.

380
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:17,750
Arata Miyako.

381
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:19,000
And what's your name?

382
00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:24,666
Hello, Suzuka.
That's a very cute name.

383
00:17:26,375 --> 00:17:27,833
-Akane?
-Yes.

384
00:17:27,916 --> 00:17:30,208
She wants you to know
her nickname.

385
00:17:30,291 --> 00:17:32,083
She'd like us all
to call her Suzu.

386
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:36,500
You really can understand
what she's saying, can't you?

387
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:42,333
♪

388
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:45,541
Okay... Suzu.

389
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:47,500
[AKANE gasps]

390
00:17:53,458 --> 00:17:54,708
[ARATA]
Now, Miss Suzu.

391
00:17:54,791 --> 00:17:56,791
Can you tell me
who stole your hair?

392
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:59,125
-Do you know them?
-You can get it back?

393
00:18:00,666 --> 00:18:02,708
[SUZUKA]
I don't think you should.

394
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:06,291
It was stolen by a beast
hiding in human form.

395
00:18:06,375 --> 00:18:10,000
It's truly a beautiful
and cheerful dark creature.

396
00:18:10,083 --> 00:18:12,375
But it's so... so scary.

397
00:18:13,791 --> 00:18:14,875
[ARATA]
Sounds like it.

398
00:18:14,958 --> 00:18:16,583
Do you know
why they took your hair?

399
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:19,458
[SUZUKA]
I don't know.

400
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:23,500
But they said
it would be over very soon.

401
00:18:24,875 --> 00:18:26,041
[YUKI meows]

402
00:18:27,125 --> 00:18:28,250
[meow]

403
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:30,541
She said it's a "beast
in human form."

404
00:18:30,625 --> 00:18:32,416
-Wow.
-Oh, yeah.

405
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,500
That reminds me of what
the fairies were saying.

406
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:37,250
FEMALE NEWSREADER:
A theft has been reported

407
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:39,500
at a Shinjuku
imported goods store.

408
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:42,250
The police are treating
the situation like a burglary.

409
00:18:43,291 --> 00:18:44,583
The case was reopened after...

410
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:46,541
Hey, look,
isn't that Koseido?

411
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:48,500
Have you heard of it?

412
00:18:48,583 --> 00:18:50,041
Well, yeah.

413
00:18:50,125 --> 00:18:52,500
It's technically
an imported goods store

414
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:55,250
but with the ability to get us
any magical stuff we need.

415
00:18:56,625 --> 00:18:58,375
You know, like goat gallstones,

416
00:18:58,458 --> 00:19:01,375
and mermaid scales,
and burning glass or...

417
00:19:02,541 --> 00:19:03,666
or living iron...

418
00:19:04,666 --> 00:19:07,083
and fairy wing powder, too.

419
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:08,791
-[ARATA] Uh, Theo?
-Huh...

420
00:19:09,791 --> 00:19:11,208
[THEO]
Give me just a minute.

421
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:19,416
-Hello, good morning.
-Good morning!

422
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:22,166
Hey, how's the
dream team doing?

423
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:23,291
[THEO]
Morning.

424
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:25,875
You look exhausted.

425
00:19:25,958 --> 00:19:28,416
[THEO] Yeah, I was just
checking on something.

426
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,041
Can you still work,
or do you need to be sent home?

427
00:19:31,125 --> 00:19:32,458
Guys, I'm fine, okay!

428
00:19:32,541 --> 00:19:33,791
Let's get to Hakoneyama.

429
00:19:33,875 --> 00:19:35,041
[SENDA] Right.

430
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:36,333
Well, there've been
many strange fires

431
00:19:36,416 --> 00:19:38,083
reported at the top
of that mountain.

432
00:19:39,125 --> 00:19:41,291
Wouldn't that be
the fire department's job?

433
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:44,583
Every time the fire department
or police head out there,

434
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:46,166
they don't seem
to find anything.

435
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:48,458
And that means it's our job now.

436
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:54,916
[ARATA]
I recognize this place.

437
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,416
It's a pretty famous
occult spot, isn't it?

438
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:00,208
[KYOICHI] Yeah. It was
originally built by the Tokugawa

439
00:20:00,291 --> 00:20:02,791
and was used as
a military base during the war.

440
00:20:02,875 --> 00:20:05,125
I've heard there was also
a hospital built under it.

441
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,583
Well? Learn anything?

442
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:15,083
[THEO]
Some kind of seal or entrance.

443
00:20:15,166 --> 00:20:17,333
Hold on.
Why is it shining like that?

444
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:18,791
-[THEO gasps]
-Idiot!

445
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:22,833
[THEO groans]

446
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:25,750
Why would you touch something
before you even know what it is?

447
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:27,500
[cell phone buzzing]

448
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,625
What? I'm pretty busy
right now.

449
00:20:30,708 --> 00:20:32,750
[SENDA] Listen! I just got
a call from the police.

450
00:20:33,875 --> 00:20:37,000
You were spot on, it turns out
it was a bunch of mermaid scales

451
00:20:37,083 --> 00:20:38,750
that were stolen
from Koseido that night.

452
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:41,916
[gasps]

453
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,833
[THEO]
Dirt from an old grave.

454
00:20:43,916 --> 00:20:45,166
Could it be?

455
00:20:46,708 --> 00:20:47,666
[switch clicks]

456
00:20:48,875 --> 00:20:49,791
[ARATA grunts]

457
00:20:49,875 --> 00:20:51,125
Ow!

458
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:52,875
-[KYOICHI] Not sorry. You awake?
-Huh?

459
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:54,791
Yeah.

460
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:58,291
Where are we?

461
00:20:58,375 --> 00:21:00,250
[KYOICHI]
Probably inside of Hakoneyama.

462
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:04,000
And judging by
how high that ceiling is,

463
00:21:04,083 --> 00:21:06,625
I'm gonna guess
we're pretty far down.

464
00:21:06,708 --> 00:21:08,500
-Know what else?
-What?

465
00:21:08,583 --> 00:21:10,125
This is why you
never touch anything

466
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:12,833
without being completely
certain it's safe.

467
00:21:12,916 --> 00:21:13,875
Got that, rookie?

468
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:14,875
[groans]

469
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:16,250
I'm so sorry.

470
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:18,375
-Huh?
-It's Seimei!

471
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:21,291
Good to see you!
It's been ages.

472
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:25,458
An Another?

473
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:31,958
What good timing you have.

474
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:34,666
The gift I brought for you
is almost finished.

475
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:37,125
What do you mean? A gift?

476
00:21:37,208 --> 00:21:38,833
[doors opening]

477
00:21:44,250 --> 00:21:45,583
Good, they're moving.

478
00:21:47,208 --> 00:21:48,333
[ARATA]
What's moving?

479
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:54,291
People?

480
00:21:54,375 --> 00:21:56,875
No. Not quite.

481
00:21:56,958 --> 00:21:59,041
They're moving corpses.
Kyoshi!

482
00:21:59,125 --> 00:22:00,750
[growls]

483
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:03,583
[ANOTHER] Did I choose the
perfect reunion gift or what?

484
00:22:05,583 --> 00:22:09,541
I hope this brings you hours
of entertainment, Seimei.

485
00:23:40,708 --> 00:23:43,083
[wind whistling]

